WEBVTT

00:00:06.060 --> 00:00:08.060
<i>I time leaped, over and over,</i>

00:00:09.100 --> 00:00:10.970
<i>to save Mayuri.</i>

00:00:15.970 --> 00:00:17.170
<i>But...</i>

00:00:18.770 --> 00:00:21.140
<i>No matter what I did,</i>

00:00:22.220 --> 00:00:22.930
<i>Mayuri...</i>

00:00:24.390 --> 00:00:25.270
<i>died.</i>

00:00:41.510 --> 00:00:44.280
<i>Even if Moeka and SERN never attacked,</i>

00:00:45.280 --> 00:00:47.660
<i>it was like fate itself kept murdering her...</i>

00:00:48.610 --> 00:00:52.470
<i>Like the entire world</i>

00:00:54.070 --> 00:00:57.350
<i>was conspiring to kill her.</i>

00:01:01.310 --> 00:01:04.100
The cars aren't moving!

00:01:04.100 --> 00:01:05.930
The train's stopped.

00:01:05.930 --> 00:01:07.180
Hurry!

00:01:07.180 --> 00:01:08.520
Take a back road or something!

00:01:08.520 --> 00:01:10.210
That's not really an option, sir.

00:01:11.470 --> 00:01:14.930
Huh? Mayushii's watch isn't working...

00:01:15.600 --> 00:01:16.920
That's strange.

00:01:16.920 --> 00:01:18.380
I just wound it.

00:01:18.380 --> 00:01:19.660
<i>Again...</i>
I just wound it.

00:01:19.660 --> 00:01:20.890
<i>Again!</i>

00:01:28.700 --> 00:01:29.590
Mayuri!

00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:38.060
Shiina Mayuri was the one who died.

00:01:38.060 --> 00:01:39.490
Okabe-kun...

00:01:39.490 --> 00:01:43.280
I mean, Okabe Rintarou has been captured.

00:01:49.280 --> 00:01:51.190
<i>No matter what I did,</i>

00:01:51.850 --> 00:01:53.930
<i>no matter what I try,</i>

00:01:54.420 --> 00:01:55.760
<i>she dies.</i>

00:01:56.670 --> 00:01:59.680
<i>It's like fate...</i>

00:01:59.680 --> 00:02:01.990
<i>I see. So this is...</i>

00:02:03.770 --> 00:02:05.550
<i>No, there's nothing like that!</i>

00:02:06.210 --> 00:02:09.220
<i>The Organization... Steins Gate...</i>

00:02:10.650 --> 00:02:12.310
<i>And fate!</i>

00:02:14.180 --> 00:02:17.930
<i>There's no such thing!</i>

00:03:47.850 --> 00:03:52.850
Physically Necrosis

00:03:53.170 --> 00:03:54.890
What do you mean?

00:03:54.890 --> 00:03:56.060
Explain!

00:03:56.060 --> 00:03:58.570
I just got to the individual character route.

00:03:58.570 --> 00:03:59.840
At least let me save—

00:03:59.840 --> 00:04:01.110
I'll do it.

00:04:01.110 --> 00:04:03.570
Just get out of Akihabara.

00:04:03.570 --> 00:04:04.180
Got it?

00:04:04.180 --> 00:04:05.460
Okabe...

00:04:33.290 --> 00:04:36.560
<i>It's after Mayuri's left.</i>

00:04:38.890 --> 00:04:40.260
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:04:41.080 --> 00:04:43.740
<i>No matter how many times I try to save her,</i>

00:04:43.740 --> 00:04:44.910
<i>in the end...</i>

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:47.480
From: Assistant 
Subject: Did something happen? 
Tell me later, okay?

00:04:47.480 --> 00:04:49.130
<i>Even the message is the same.</i>
From: Assistant 
Subject: Did something happen? 
Tell me later, okay?

00:04:49.130 --> 00:04:49.750
From: Assistant 
Subject: Did something happen? 
Tell me later, okay?

00:04:49.750 --> 00:04:50.430
<i>The message.</i>
From: Assistant 
Subject: Did something happen? 
Tell me later, okay?

00:04:53.880 --> 00:04:55.480
"Shining Finger."

00:04:56.190 --> 00:04:59.560
"I have new information 
regarding the time machine."

00:05:00.560 --> 00:05:02.520
"I'd like to talk to you alone."

00:05:14.270 --> 00:05:15.720
Don't move.

00:05:16.470 --> 00:05:17.470
Put your hands up.

00:05:24.340 --> 00:05:25.680
Who are you people?!

00:05:34.940 --> 00:05:35.950
Part-time job.

00:05:35.950 --> 00:05:37.190
Arc rewrite.

00:05:37.550 --> 00:05:43.560
I know you're planning 
to attack the lab and kidnap us!

00:05:45.290 --> 00:05:46.000
How?

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:47.600
Because I've come from the future!

00:05:47.600 --> 00:05:48.840
Do you understand?

00:05:48.840 --> 00:05:50.120
Now answer me!

00:05:50.920 --> 00:05:51.770
My phone...

00:05:51.770 --> 00:05:52.570
No!

00:05:52.570 --> 00:05:53.870
Answer me now...

00:05:53.870 --> 00:05:55.610
Are you with SERN?

00:05:55.610 --> 00:05:56.670
Rounder.

00:05:56.670 --> 00:05:57.600
Rounder?

00:05:57.600 --> 00:06:00.520
Our mission is to recover the IBN 5100.

00:06:01.170 --> 00:06:02.980
You're the one who stole it!

00:06:03.410 --> 00:06:04.410
I don't know anything.

00:06:04.410 --> 00:06:05.460
Don't try tricking me!

00:06:05.460 --> 00:06:07.530
You sent that D-mail...

00:06:08.530 --> 00:06:09.670
<i>I get it.</i>

00:06:09.670 --> 00:06:11.410
<i>The world line changed,</i>

00:06:11.410 --> 00:06:14.770
<i>so she has no memory of sending that message.</i>

00:06:15.250 --> 00:06:16.740
Why do you plan to attack the lab?

00:06:16.740 --> 00:06:19.850
The IBN 5100 isn't there anymore.

00:06:20.280 --> 00:06:20.950
Too late.

00:06:20.950 --> 00:06:22.020
Answer me!

00:06:22.550 --> 00:06:24.350
Three reasons.

00:06:25.070 --> 00:06:26.280
One.

00:06:26.740 --> 00:06:29.530
You've learned something 
you can't be allowed to know.

00:06:31.280 --> 00:06:32.580
Two.

00:06:33.050 --> 00:06:35.480
You made a time machine.

00:06:37.870 --> 00:06:39.270
Three.

00:06:39.940 --> 00:06:42.140
You wanted to publicly announce it.

00:06:45.020 --> 00:06:46.900
You knew all that...

00:06:47.660 --> 00:06:49.960
Does SERN know?

00:06:51.380 --> 00:06:54.100
My orders come from FB.

00:06:54.100 --> 00:06:55.360
FB?

00:06:55.360 --> 00:06:57.240
Is that an organization within SERN?

00:06:59.320 --> 00:07:03.830
FB is everything to me...

00:07:06.440 --> 00:07:07.860
<i>Where am I?</i>

00:07:08.940 --> 00:07:09.840
Don't move.

00:07:10.890 --> 00:07:13.860
Are you John Titor?

00:07:15.410 --> 00:07:18.100
You're the only person it could be...

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:19.930
No!

00:07:29.640 --> 00:07:30.780
Where am I?

00:07:30.780 --> 00:07:34.320
The bomb threat has halted all the trains.

00:07:34.320 --> 00:07:35.520
According to plan.

00:07:38.590 --> 00:07:41.470
Capture Makise Kurisu and Hashida Itaru.

00:07:41.470 --> 00:07:43.030
No one else is needed.

00:07:43.030 --> 00:07:43.750
Wait!

00:07:46.170 --> 00:07:48.150
W-Wait!

00:07:48.150 --> 00:07:51.600
Please don't kill Mayuri!

00:07:53.520 --> 00:07:54.530
I'm sorry!

00:07:55.260 --> 00:07:56.310
I was wrong!

00:07:56.980 --> 00:07:59.810
I never wanted to expose SERN!

00:07:59.810 --> 00:08:01.890
I'll give you the time leap machine...

00:08:01.890 --> 00:08:04.170
I'll never tell anyone what I learned!

00:08:04.170 --> 00:08:05.770
Begin the mission.

00:08:05.770 --> 00:08:07.870
Please! I'll do anything!

00:08:07.870 --> 00:08:10.820
Please... It was just simple curiosity...

00:08:10.820 --> 00:08:12.930
It was a game!

00:08:12.930 --> 00:08:15.770
So... Just spare Mayuri...

00:08:16.720 --> 00:08:18.520
It's too late.

00:08:22.600 --> 00:08:23.570
Mayuri...

00:08:26.930 --> 00:08:29.020
Mayuri!

00:08:29.320 --> 00:08:30.680
Shut up!

00:08:31.580 --> 00:08:32.560
Mayuri!

00:08:38.030 --> 00:08:39.270
Mayuri...

00:08:57.840 --> 00:08:59.240
What's wrong?

00:09:00.480 --> 00:09:02.560
Were you napping?

00:09:03.240 --> 00:09:04.660
This again...

00:09:09.470 --> 00:09:11.730
I can't take this anymore!

00:09:11.730 --> 00:09:12.970
Okabe!

00:09:14.270 --> 00:09:15.140
What's wrong?

00:09:17.010 --> 00:09:18.770
You don't need to destroy it.

00:09:18.770 --> 00:09:21.650
We decided we aren't doing the time leap.

00:09:23.250 --> 00:09:25.210
What's wrong with you, all of a sudden?

00:09:25.210 --> 00:09:27.970
You're going shopping, for the party, right?

00:09:29.550 --> 00:09:30.820
The party...

00:09:32.080 --> 00:09:33.850
Wait, Okabe!

00:09:36.440 --> 00:09:38.520
It's the bullet train!

00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:42.100
No, the bullet train is white.

00:09:44.560 --> 00:09:47.050
Oka... Kyouma-san...

00:09:50.110 --> 00:09:51.490
Where's Mayuri?

00:09:51.490 --> 00:09:53.560
Mayuri-chan already left.

00:09:53.560 --> 00:09:54.520
I know.

00:09:55.480 --> 00:09:57.750
I know she came to invite you to the party...

00:09:57.750 --> 00:10:02.410
And that she's going to meet 
her friend who cosplays...

00:10:02.410 --> 00:10:05.970
I know she's looking forward to the party.

00:10:06.790 --> 00:10:08.590
All of it!

00:10:14.660 --> 00:10:16.420
I'm sorry.

00:10:17.680 --> 00:10:18.900
But I...

00:10:20.170 --> 00:10:21.520
But I...

00:10:27.370 --> 00:10:29.390
What are you doing over there?

00:10:33.220 --> 00:10:34.520
Kurisu...

00:10:34.960 --> 00:10:37.800
That's the first time you've ever 
called me by the right name.

00:10:37.800 --> 00:10:38.890
What happened?

00:10:38.890 --> 00:10:40.720
No, what's going to happen?

00:10:44.050 --> 00:10:46.810
You time leaped, didn't you?

00:10:47.850 --> 00:10:49.120
It's all...

00:10:49.120 --> 00:10:50.640
All my fault.

00:10:50.640 --> 00:10:51.310
Okabe.

00:10:52.770 --> 00:10:54.850
It's all my fault.

00:10:56.040 --> 00:10:58.850
I never should have told
 Daru to hack into SERN.

00:10:59.760 --> 00:11:02.870
I never should have said to 
make the time machine.

00:11:02.870 --> 00:11:05.860
I never should have invited 
Moeka to be a lab member!

00:11:05.860 --> 00:11:08.350
It's my fault... And Mayuri...

00:11:14.950 --> 00:11:17.250
You're pushing yourself too hard, idiot.

00:11:18.350 --> 00:11:22.270
We don't know that the time leap 
machine is completely safe.

00:11:22.270 --> 00:11:26.340
It's possible you could completely 
erase yourself from existence.

00:11:26.340 --> 00:11:29.970
On a fundamental level, 
humans are temporal creatures.

00:11:30.380 --> 00:11:33.810
Heidegger... I was just about to say that.

00:11:35.150 --> 00:11:37.180
I learned that phrase from you.

00:11:38.150 --> 00:11:40.470
That's kind of creepy.

00:11:40.470 --> 00:11:42.850
It's like you're peeking inside my head.

00:11:42.850 --> 00:11:47.100
But I guess that's what a time leap is.

00:11:48.210 --> 00:11:50.420
What should I do?

00:11:51.070 --> 00:11:53.070
When will the lab be attacked?

00:11:53.070 --> 00:11:54.350
After 7:30.

00:11:55.350 --> 00:12:00.020
I can think of several possible 
causes for Mayuri's death.

00:12:00.020 --> 00:12:02.970
But we don't have time to talk.

00:12:04.210 --> 00:12:05.350
Let's go.

00:12:05.730 --> 00:12:07.560
Mayuri's a dear friend.

00:12:07.560 --> 00:12:08.890
I want to save her, too!

00:12:11.420 --> 00:12:12.350
I'm sorry.

00:12:12.350 --> 00:12:14.360
Don't apologize.

00:12:14.360 --> 00:12:15.900
I want to help you.

00:12:16.370 --> 00:12:17.180
I do...

00:12:18.600 --> 00:12:22.120
Hey, mad scientist!

00:12:22.120 --> 00:12:24.470
You're going to change the world, right?

00:12:27.050 --> 00:12:28.200
Of course!

00:12:34.550 --> 00:12:35.390
Right?

00:12:52.070 --> 00:12:54.430
I set the time to five or so hours ago,

00:12:54.430 --> 00:12:57.890
to just when the time leap machine was created.

00:12:58.670 --> 00:13:02.720
If you go to before it's completed, 
it's possible I won't finish it.

00:13:06.570 --> 00:13:08.280
You go back in time,

00:13:08.280 --> 00:13:10.430
and once the time leap machine is done,

00:13:10.430 --> 00:13:13.310
send everyone away and 
tell me what we just discussed.

00:13:14.070 --> 00:13:15.690
If you say you've come from the future,

00:13:15.690 --> 00:13:17.390
I'll probably believe it.

00:13:17.390 --> 00:13:18.390
How can you know?

00:13:19.100 --> 00:13:22.110
I know myself better than anyone.

00:13:22.110 --> 00:13:25.460
I'm the one who made the time leap machine,

00:13:25.460 --> 00:13:26.850
to begin with.

00:13:28.330 --> 00:13:30.930
You mean you're confident about your work?

00:13:30.930 --> 00:13:32.170
I guess so.

00:13:32.170 --> 00:13:35.070
When I saw you back there, I was certain.

00:13:35.070 --> 00:13:37.300
That you'd time leaped, I mean.

00:13:38.340 --> 00:13:40.770
Just in case, let's decide on a keyword.

00:13:41.940 --> 00:13:44.030
Right now, what I want most is

00:13:44.030 --> 00:13:45.570
my own personal fork.

00:13:46.480 --> 00:13:47.710
You want one?

00:13:48.400 --> 00:13:49.470
A fork?

00:13:49.470 --> 00:13:52.370
Yeah, I already have a personal spoon.

00:13:52.370 --> 00:13:54.970
Don't be nosy about that!

00:13:55.560 --> 00:13:56.680
Here we go!

00:13:58.060 --> 00:13:58.680
Okay.

00:14:01.160 --> 00:14:02.890
Five hours ago,

00:14:03.430 --> 00:14:08.100
I won't remember that you called me Kurisu...

00:14:17.980 --> 00:14:20.810
Do you think you could hold this?

00:14:21.510 --> 00:14:22.450
Like this?

00:14:22.450 --> 00:14:23.310
That's right.

00:14:23.310 --> 00:14:26.420
Keep it spread out like that!

00:14:28.270 --> 00:14:30.270
That ribbon's cute.

00:14:30.270 --> 00:14:31.650
Right?

00:14:31.650 --> 00:14:34.040
Want to try it on?

00:14:34.040 --> 00:14:36.520
I still have some cosplay outfits for Comima.

00:14:37.480 --> 00:14:38.930
Cosplay, huh?

00:14:38.930 --> 00:14:41.100
Interested?

00:14:41.100 --> 00:14:42.890
N-No way!

00:14:43.550 --> 00:14:45.670
I couldn't wear this around others...

00:14:47.430 --> 00:14:48.980
<i>I see...</i>

00:14:48.980 --> 00:14:52.570
<i>Five hours ago, Mayuri hasn't left.</i>

00:14:52.570 --> 00:14:55.930
<i>As I recall, her cosplay outfit's finished
right as the time leap machine's done.</i>

00:14:57.610 --> 00:14:59.140
It's done!

00:15:00.550 --> 00:15:02.300
I win!

00:15:02.300 --> 00:15:03.980
We were racing.

00:15:03.980 --> 00:15:05.760
I lose.

00:15:05.760 --> 00:15:08.290
But we're almost done, too.

00:15:08.290 --> 00:15:09.760
Now we're done.

00:15:10.810 --> 00:15:11.560
This is...

00:15:11.560 --> 00:15:13.250
We won't do the experiment!

00:15:17.170 --> 00:15:19.100
<i>Darn... Was that too sudden?</i>

00:15:19.100 --> 00:15:20.350
What do you mean?

00:15:21.600 --> 00:15:24.570
Y-You're all tired.

00:15:24.570 --> 00:15:25.600
We'll talk later.

00:15:26.280 --> 00:15:28.060
We're done for today.

00:15:31.430 --> 00:15:32.470
I'll take a plate.

00:15:32.470 --> 00:15:33.700
One plate.

00:15:33.700 --> 00:15:35.100
What are you doing here?

00:15:35.100 --> 00:15:38.400
I'd just ordered when I got your message.

00:15:38.400 --> 00:15:41.030
I didn't think you were a regular here.

00:15:41.030 --> 00:15:43.440
I-I'm not a regular!

00:15:43.440 --> 00:15:45.440
Mayuri told me about this place.

00:15:45.440 --> 00:15:47.870
So what did you want to talk about?

00:15:47.870 --> 00:15:50.110
You told us all to leave, and then

00:15:50.110 --> 00:15:52.470
you suddenly message me.

00:15:52.760 --> 00:15:53.880
You see...

00:15:55.940 --> 00:15:58.310
I've come from five hours in the future.

00:15:58.310 --> 00:16:01.060
What? That's the stupidest line I've ever heard.

00:16:02.180 --> 00:16:05.690
H-Hey! That isn't what you said!

00:16:05.690 --> 00:16:07.870
You said you'd probably believe me!

00:16:07.870 --> 00:16:10.050
What are you talking about?

00:16:10.050 --> 00:16:11.610
Probably? Believe you?

00:16:11.610 --> 00:16:14.810
I wouldn't say anything that illogical.

00:16:14.810 --> 00:16:16.320
You did say it!

00:16:16.320 --> 00:16:20.010
"I'm the one who made the 
time leap machine, to begin with."

00:16:20.010 --> 00:16:21.070
You looked really proud, too!

00:16:21.650 --> 00:16:23.150
Are you a moron?

00:16:23.150 --> 00:16:25.100
Whatever...

00:16:26.640 --> 00:16:28.600
<i>I really want to smack her...</i>

00:16:32.320 --> 00:16:34.370
Right now, what you want most is

00:16:34.370 --> 00:16:35.430
your own personal fork.

00:16:36.810 --> 00:16:37.640
Well?

00:16:37.640 --> 00:16:39.820
I really told you that?

00:16:39.820 --> 00:16:41.310
The five-hours-from-now me?

00:16:42.370 --> 00:16:44.810
You said you already had your own spoon.

00:16:46.030 --> 00:16:48.310
Screw you, future me...

00:16:48.310 --> 00:16:50.930
You believe me now, right?

00:16:52.390 --> 00:16:56.470
Yeah... So the machine 
works just as I predicted.

00:16:56.800 --> 00:16:58.640
It's perfect.

00:17:00.230 --> 00:17:01.850
Here's your plate.

00:17:03.300 --> 00:17:04.790
I see.

00:17:04.790 --> 00:17:08.000
If all that's true, it's really bad.

00:17:08.000 --> 00:17:08.810
Yeah.

00:17:09.220 --> 00:17:12.220
Rather than help Mayuri escape, 
have you tried stopping Moeka-san...

00:17:12.220 --> 00:17:13.850
A Rounder, you called her?

00:17:13.850 --> 00:17:16.390
Stopping her group and her?

00:17:16.390 --> 00:17:17.580
I did.

00:17:18.150 --> 00:17:21.350
But I couldn't stop Mayuri's death.

00:17:21.960 --> 00:17:23.000
I see.

00:17:25.260 --> 00:17:28.870
For something to occur, it must have a cause.

00:17:28.870 --> 00:17:30.350
<——                          Effect
Cause 
Death
For something to occur, it must have a cause.

00:17:30.370 --> 00:17:32.470
Death

00:17:32.960 --> 00:17:35.920
Normally, death would be preceded

00:17:35.920 --> 00:17:38.050
by some proximate phenomenon,

00:17:38.050 --> 00:17:41.170
like an accident or an illness.

00:17:41.170 --> 00:17:43.680
But we can't determine the cause for sure.

00:17:44.040 --> 00:17:48.210
The Rounders are the 
proximate cause of Mayuri's death,

00:17:48.210 --> 00:17:50.220
but the real cause is likely different.

00:17:50.640 --> 00:17:53.180
So even if the Rounders never appear,

00:17:53.180 --> 00:17:54.430
Mayuri still dies.

00:17:54.430 --> 00:17:56.390
Then, what's the cause?
<——                          Effect
Cause 
Death

00:17:56.720 --> 00:17:57.930
I don't know.

00:17:57.930 --> 00:18:01.370
It's possible that the cause of Mayuri's death

00:18:01.370 --> 00:18:04.680
is Mayuri's own birth.

00:18:04.680 --> 00:18:06.790
You mean her life span's run out?

00:18:07.230 --> 00:18:09.170
That's fatalism!

00:18:09.170 --> 00:18:09.960
Indeed.

00:18:09.960 --> 00:18:12.060
So I won't suggest it.

00:18:12.060 --> 00:18:13.820
The cause should be something

00:18:13.820 --> 00:18:16.140
that initiated this series of events.

00:18:16.850 --> 00:18:18.060
<i>Initiated...</i>

00:18:22.240 --> 00:18:25.220
Is it possible that if this 
isn't completed, Mayuri would...

00:18:25.220 --> 00:18:26.410
Wait.

00:18:26.410 --> 00:18:28.890
It's dangerous to jump to conclusions!

00:18:28.890 --> 00:18:30.060
But...

00:18:30.060 --> 00:18:32.310
Makise Kurisu is right.

00:18:34.310 --> 00:18:35.740
You're...

00:18:35.740 --> 00:18:37.020
Do you know something?

00:18:37.020 --> 00:18:39.480
You're more or less correct.

00:18:39.480 --> 00:18:41.760
Fixing everything won't be as easy

00:18:41.760 --> 00:18:44.350
as not completing the time leap machine.

00:18:44.350 --> 00:18:46.450
To save the world,

00:18:46.450 --> 00:18:48.100
you need to reach world line beta.

00:18:48.750 --> 00:18:53.340
You must cross the 1% divergence barrier.

00:18:54.490 --> 00:18:56.350
The divergence number

00:18:56.350 --> 00:18:59.570
indicates this world line's location.

00:18:59.970 --> 00:19:02.890
And the only clue we have as to what it is,

00:19:03.240 --> 00:19:05.810
is this divergence meter.

00:19:06.120 --> 00:19:07.820
Nixie Tubes? {D: TC - I couldn't find this name anywhere, and it's kind of weird. Anything you can dig up to verify? I think it's a future gadget he's not created yet}

00:19:07.820 --> 00:19:09.630
Whoever made it has good taste.

00:19:09.630 --> 00:19:11.130
Of course they do.

00:19:11.130 --> 00:19:13.360
You're the one who made it.

00:19:13.740 --> 00:19:14.270
I did?

00:19:14.720 --> 00:19:17.280
You have the power to retain

00:19:17.280 --> 00:19:20.140
your memories, when moving world lines.

00:19:20.720 --> 00:19:23.180
In the future, you made this meter

00:19:23.180 --> 00:19:24.680
to numerically display

00:19:24.680 --> 00:19:28.920
the difference between this world line 
and the previous one you inhabited.

00:19:29.280 --> 00:19:32.310
0.337187...

00:19:32.310 --> 00:19:34.270
That's this world line.

00:19:34.680 --> 00:19:40.050
A world line is like a woven braid or this rope.

00:19:43.460 --> 00:19:46.120
This rope looks like it's a single line,

00:19:46.120 --> 00:19:50.400
but actually, many thin threads comprise it.

00:19:50.400 --> 00:19:51.990
The threads are the world lines.

00:19:52.590 --> 00:19:55.510
Each never touches the others,

00:19:55.510 --> 00:19:58.220
but they all go to the same place.

00:19:59.070 --> 00:20:00.140
In other words,

00:20:00.140 --> 00:20:03.590
they all tend toward a world in which Mayuri dies...

00:20:05.640 --> 00:20:08.670
But if the world line drastically changes,

00:20:08.670 --> 00:20:12.150
from our alpha world line to the beta world line,

00:20:12.150 --> 00:20:14.040
over the 1% barrier,

00:20:14.040 --> 00:20:15.760
another outcome would occur.

00:20:15.760 --> 00:20:18.390
You guys use that one.

00:20:18.860 --> 00:20:19.880
Wait.

00:20:19.880 --> 00:20:22.020
I can't climb up, just using that.

00:20:22.020 --> 00:20:24.000
Oh, fine...

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:25.720
Just wait here.

00:20:35.590 --> 00:20:37.180
Who is Amane-san, anyway?

00:20:37.180 --> 00:20:39.060
She's definitely a professional.

00:20:39.060 --> 00:20:40.260
Of some kind.

00:20:45.610 --> 00:20:46.690
Let's go.

00:20:46.690 --> 00:20:47.850
Hurry.

00:20:48.730 --> 00:20:51.350
The alpha and beta world lines

00:20:51.350 --> 00:20:55.650
are world lines with completely different results.

00:20:55.650 --> 00:20:57.850
Normally, it's impossible to move between them.

00:20:58.430 --> 00:20:59.920
Even if you change the past,

00:20:59.920 --> 00:21:01.670
using the time leap and the D-mail,

00:21:01.670 --> 00:21:03.400
you couldn't do it.

00:21:03.400 --> 00:21:06.630
But in several years, major events occur,

00:21:06.630 --> 00:21:12.020
and the choices made then split 
the world into multiple world lines.

00:21:12.020 --> 00:21:16.460
Recently, it would be 1991, 
when the Gulf War occurred.

00:21:16.460 --> 00:21:18.600
And 2000, with the Y2K problem.

00:21:18.600 --> 00:21:22.640
And 2010, when the time machine was created.

00:21:26.310 --> 00:21:27.810
This is...

00:21:28.720 --> 00:21:30.800
When the split occurs,

00:21:30.800 --> 00:21:34.720
it's possible to move from 
the alpha world line to the beta.

00:21:34.720 --> 00:21:36.710
How is it done?

00:21:36.710 --> 00:21:37.400
How—

00:21:37.400 --> 00:21:38.380
Wait!

00:21:39.130 --> 00:21:40.400
Before that,

00:21:40.820 --> 00:21:42.970
tell us who are you.

00:21:52.250 --> 00:21:53.620
This is...

00:21:54.020 --> 00:21:55.020
A time machine.

00:21:56.600 --> 00:22:00.060
I'm from the year 2036.

00:22:00.060 --> 00:22:01.680
Suzuha...

00:22:02.190 --> 00:22:04.520
I am the time traveler

00:22:05.010 --> 00:22:06.930
John Titor.

